  "description": [
    "PAYTON CCUEfN FAIR FEARLESS Vol 6No 34 r The CHICAGO FLIGHT OFFICERS PLANE CRASH VICTIMS AT TUSKEGEE TUSKEGEE May 2 ANP Flight Officers Sylvester H Hurd Jr and George A Bates pilots at Tuskegee Army Air field were killed here when the single engine trainer in which they were on a routine flight crashed near Mil stead Ala Cause of the crash has not yet been determined but a board has been appointed to investigate the accident Flight Officer Hurd who re ceived his pilot wings here last No vember was the son of Sylvester H Hurd Sr of East Chicago and Flight Officer Bates a March TAAF graduate was the son of Mrs Grace C Bates of Chicago Both officers were undergoing con tinuation training according to Col_Parrish commanding officer here SPINGARN MEDAL TO THURGOOD MARSHALL NEW YORK May 2 ANP Thurgood Marshall NAACP spe cial counsel was named the 31st recipient of the Spingarn medal awarded annually for highest achievement by a Negro The noted lawyer received the 1946 award for distinguished service as a lawyer particularly in the Texas Primary case which may have more far reaching influence than any other act in the ending of disfranchise"
